properties.areaDesc: Natrona County Lower Elevations; Green Mountains and Rattlesnake Range
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 1 at 12:26AM MST until January 1 at 3:00PM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...High Wind Warning through 3 PM Wednesday for Southeast Fremont
and Natrona Counties...

.A very tight pressure gradient is resulting in strong to high
wind across portions of southeast Fremont into Natrona counties
late tonight and Wednesday.

* WHAT...Southwest winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts 50 to 60 mph.
Locally higher gusts around 70 mph are expected along Outer
Drive on the south side of Casper, and on ridge tops in
southeast Fremont County.

* WHERE...Green Mountains and Rattlesnake Range and Natrona County
Lower Elevations. This includes Interstate 25.

* WHEN...Until 3 PM MST this afternoon. The strongest winds will
occur through 9 AM, but remain windy all day.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. There is an elevated risk
for a blow over for light and high profile vehicles, including
campers and tractor trailers. Please consider delaying travel if
your driving such a vehicle.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Please keep two hands on your steering
wheel in case of a sudden, strong wind gust.
properties.instruction:
People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around
trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of
your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Use caution if
you must drive.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 PM MST THIS AFTERNOON
